snippet.textDisplay:
Huge fan of Donut, but posting this video to YT is a real low-blow to the entire plasti dip industry.

This was originally uploaded to Donut's Facebook on August 19, 2019. Immediately after, Fonzie of DipYourCar posted a reaction video that can be seen here: www.youtube.com/watch?v=GrIRYABrCTM. I encourage everyone to watch it - Fonzie delivers the most respectful criticism I've ever seen.
To summarize - Donut failed horribly by doing zero research. While this may highlight an "amateur " application, I sure know that I'd do more reading before dropping $600 to plasti dip my baby!
Nolan applied self-mixed, 10 year old paint through the completely wrong spray gun. He sprayed from way too far off the car, and didn't allow proper drying time. The old paint & wrong gun 100% explain the thin, runny mess they applied. Plasti dip has come a long way in the last decade!

Fonzie explained this all very professionally, and even offered to collaborate & re-spray the car to teach Donut-fans how to plasti dip. Nolan commented on that video, agreeing they messed up, and stated he'd love to re-spray the car in the future.


Why, then, did Donut upload this video to YT in January 2020, spreading the same misinformation about the plasti dip industry 5 months later? They should have filmed a re-spray video! Instead, they added a brief voice-over explanation at the 5:50 mark.... That's not good enough in my opinion. Yet here they are, with another 1million+ views.... They owe Fonzie an apology!
